<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4598579>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 5. Arachnids. A−E. Two fragments of the same piece containing portion of a spider egg sac, shown in different views and magnifications (AMNH LC-B3a, b). D, E. Highest magnification, showing how silk strands are cabled and woven. F. Spider (unidentified), ventral view (AMNH LC-D7). G. Pseudoscorpion, family indet. AMNH GC-A8b. H. Mite, Acari: Oribatida (family indet.), ventral view (AMNH LC-D1). See figure 7D for another spider inclusion." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4598579/files/figure.png" .

